With this code: 

    var contents = divToPrint.html();

`contents` is now a string - you need to convert this to a jquery object:

    var contents = $(divToPrint.html());

you can then manipulate this variable and it will update the variable, eg:

    contents.find(&quot;span&quot;).removeClass(&quot;overflow-hidden&quot;);

if you use `$(contents).find...` then it will create a new jquery variable each time and update that - i.e. not update `contents`.

To get the final html:

    sendToOutput(contents.html());
